^B@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|A penalty double says 'Partner, stay out of my way. I have them right where I want them.' But when you make a takeout double and then double again, you are saying you have extra values. You have a strong takeout double. You already said you were short in the opponent's suit. Your distribution did not change halfway through the hand. So your partner is entitled to bid.|
